						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up at the entrance into the compound of the Vishṇu temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1760, Viḷambi, Vaiśākha śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1838, May 9, Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>It records the setting up of a <hi rend="italic">dhvaja-staṁbha</hi> and celebration of the <hi rend="italic">garuḍotsava</hi> of the god Chennakēśava by Lakshmamma, wife of Subbarāya, son of Rāghava and grandson of Prabhākara-Narāyaṇappa, of the Āpastaṁba-sūtra and Kāśyapa-gōtra.</p>						

						</summary>
